The Gallorommatidae is a family of microscopic hymenopteran insects, known from five fossil species in a single genus, Galloromma. These are Galloromma agapa from the Taimyr amber, Galloromma alavaensis from the Escucha Formation, Galloromma bezonnaisensis from French amber, Galloromma kachinensis from Burmese amber and Galloromma turolensis also from the Eschucha Formation.